### Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080
@phoneAdmin = +33677777777
@phoneNormal = +33688888888

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### STORY ADMIN-ROLE — Tests du système de rôles
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
###
### - Register classique : crée un compte role = USER.
### - Endpoint bootstrap POST /users/register/admin : crée le PREMIER admin.
###   - Refuse (409) si un admin existe déjà.
### - Migration Flyway V2 ajoute la colonne `role` aux DB existantes.
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### SETUP — register + login both users first (so tokens are populated)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Register a normal user (role USER by default, expects 200)
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "NormalUser",
  "password": "test123",
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneNormal}}",
  "email": "normal@test.com"
}

### 2. Bootstrap admin (expects 201 on first run, 400 afterwards because the phone is now in use — see #5 for the 409 case)
POST {{host}}/users/register/admin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "SuperAdmin",
  "password": "admin123",
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneAdmin}}",
  "email": "admin@chatapp.com"
}

### 3. Login admin → captures tokenAdmin
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneAdmin}}",
  "password": "admin123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("tokenAdmin", response.body.trim().replace(/^"|"$/g, ""));
%}

### 4. Login normal user → captures tokenUser
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneNormal}}",
  "password": "test123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("tokenUser", response.body.trim().replace(/^"|"$/g, ""));
%}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### BOOTSTRAP ADMIN — error cases
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 5. Try to create a second admin (expects 409 - an admin already exists)
POST {{host}}/users/register/admin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "SecondAdmin",
  "password": "admin123",
  "phoneNumber": "+33699999999",
  "email": "admin2@chatapp.com"
}

### 6. Try to create an admin with an already-used phone (expects 400)
POST {{host}}/users/register/admin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "DuplicateAdmin",
  "password": "admin123",
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneNormal}}",
  "email": "dup@chatapp.com"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### Admin route protection (hasRole("ADMIN") on /api/v1/admin/**)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 7. Admin → 200 OK (message logs)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/logs/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenAdmin}}

### 8. Normal user → 403 Forbidden
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/logs/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenUser}}

### 9. No token → 401 Unauthorized
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/logs/messages

### 10. Admin → 200 OK (file logs)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/logs/files
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenAdmin}}

### 11. Normal user → 403 Forbidden (file logs)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/logs/files
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenUser}}